s (TV series)|Astronauts]]''\n| Beadle\n| 13 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1983\n|''[[Philip Marlowe, Private Eye]]''\n| Don Luigi\n|Episode: ''The Pencil''\n|-\n|''[[Hart to Hart]]''\n| William Eady\n| Episode: ''Passing Chance''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1984\n| ''[[The First Olympics: Athens 1896]]'' \n| [[Francis Landey Patton|President Francis Patton]] \n| TV mini-series \n|-\n| ''[[Remington Steele]]''\n| Wallace Carlisle\n|Episode: ''Maltese Steele''\n|-\n| ''[[Ellis Island (miniseries)|Ellis Island]]''\n| Doctor Moore \n| TV mini-series\n|-\n| 1986-90\n| ''[[Howards' Way]]''\n| Robert Hudson\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1988\n| ''[[Tales of the Unexpected (TV series)|Tales of the Unexpected]]''\n| Mr. Groober \n| 1 episode\n|-\n| ''[[The Bourne Identity (1988 film)|The Bourne Identity]]''\n| Senator Crawford\n| TV mini-series\n|-\n| 1992-93\n| ''[[Road to Avonlea]]'' \n| Mr. Harrison \n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles]]''\n| [[Richard C. Kerens|Ambassador Kerens]]\n| Episode: ''Vienna, November 1908''\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Scarlett (miniseries)|Scarlett]]''\n| Minister \n| 1 episode\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[As Time Goes By (TV series)|As Time Goes By]]''\n| Young Rocky \n| 1 episode\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Kavanagh QC]]''\n| Governor Stamford Cotton \n| 1 episode \n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{findagrave|85829420}}\n*{{IMDb name|0090124|Bruce Boa}}\n* [http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/4ce2ba128c463 Bruce Boa] [[British Film Institute|BFI]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boa, Bruce}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:2004 deaths]]\n[[Category:Calgary Stampeders players]]\n[[Category:Canadian expatriates in England]]\n[[Category:Canadian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Canadian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in England]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Calgary]]\n[[Category:University of Western Ontario alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian male actors]]\n"