Volleyball Championship|2011 Tehran]]|}} \n{{MedalSilver|[[2009 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2009 Manila]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Volleyball at the Asian Games|Asian Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[Volleyball at the 2018 Asian Games \u2013 Men's tournament|2018 Jakarta-Palembang]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[Volleyball at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2014 Incheon]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[Volleyball at the 2010 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2010 Guangzhou]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|Asian Cup]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2010 Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|2010 Urmia]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2008 Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|2008 Nakhon Ratchasima]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Seyed Mohammad Mousavi Eraghi''' ({{lang-fa|\u0633\u06cc\u062f \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0645\u0648\u0633\u0648\u06cc \u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642\u06cc}}, born 22 August 1987 in [[Dezful]]) is a [[volleyball]] player from [[Iran]], who plays as a middle blocker for Polish club [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn]] and the [[Iran men's national volleyball team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=POL M: Transfer bomb! Mousavi signs with Olsztyn, will play his first season abroad|url=https://www.worldofvolley.com/Latest_news/Poland/106376/pol-m-transfer-bomb-mousavi-signs-with-olsztyn-will-play-his-first-season-abroad.html|publisher=www.worldofvolley.com|accessdate=10 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Name==\nHis family is originally from [[Arak, Iran]], and because in the past the city's name was \"[[Persian Iraq|Eragh-e Ajam]]\" (meaning Persian Iraq, or non-Arab Iraq) his family name is followed by \"Eraghi\" (Iraqi).\n\n==Career==\n\n===National team===\nMousavi was invited to national team in 2008. He was named Best Blocker at the [[2008 FIVB Men's World Olympic Qualification Tournaments|2008 Olympic Qualification Tournament]], where Iran ended up on sixth place and missed qualification for the [[Volleyball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]], [[China]]. He was named twice the Best Blocker in [[Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|Asian Championship]]. He made a brilliant performance in [[2013 FIVB Volleyball World League|2013 World League]] and was named Second Best Middle Blocker in [[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2015 World Cup]].\n\n===Clubs===\nHe started his career in volleyball club Loulehsazi Ahvaz. He played for Petrochimi Bandar Imam, [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]], [[Giti Pasand Isfahan VC|Giti Pasand Isfahan]], [[Kalleh Mazandaran VC|Kalleh Mazandaran]], [[Matin Varamin VC|Matin Vatamin]]. Mousavi has won eleven championships while playing for five teams in [[Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Super League]].\nHe has received offers to play for some of the world\u2019s leading teams, including [[Al Arabi Qatar (volleyball)|Al Arabi]] of Qatar and an unnamed Italian [[Italian Volleyball League|Serie A]] club but decided to play in Iranian League.\nHe was named the Best Blocker in [[2010 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|2010 Club World Championship]] with Paykan.\nHe played for three years in [[Sarmayeh Bank Tehran VC|Sarmayeh Bank]] until 2018.\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2010 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Qatar 2010]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n\n* '''[[AVC Club Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian Club Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2007 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Bahrain 2007]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2008 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Kazakhstan 2008]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2009 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|United Arab Emirates 2009]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2010 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|China 2010]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2013 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Iran 2013]] \u2013 with [[Kaleh Mazandaran VC|Kalleh Mazandaran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2014 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Philippines 2014]] \u2013 with [[Matin Varamin VC|Matin Varamin]]\n** [[File:Bronze medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2015 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Chinese Taipei 2015]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2016 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Myanmar 2016]] \u2013 with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2017 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|Vietnam 2017]] \u2013 with [[Sarmayeh Bank Tehran VC|Sarmayeh Bank Tehran]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2006/2007''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2006\u201307 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** '''2007/2008''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2007\u201308 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2008\u201309 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** '''2009/2010''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2009\u201310 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** '''2010/2011''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2010\u201311 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012\u201313 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Kaleh Mazandaran VC|Kalleh Mazandaran]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013\u201314 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Matin Varamin VC|Matin Varamin]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Paykan Tehran VC|Paykan Tehran]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Sarmayeh Bank Tehran VC|Sarmayeh Bank Tehran]]\n** '''2016/2017''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2016\u201317 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Sarmayeh Bank Tehran VC|Sarmayeh Bank Tehran]]\n** '''2017/2018''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2017\u201318 Iranian Volleyball Super League|Iranian Championship]], with [[Sarmayeh Bank Tehran VC|Sarmayeh Bank Tehran]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2004''' [[File:Silver medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2004 Asian Junior Men's Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian U21 Championship]]\n** '''2005''' [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2005 Asian Youth Boys Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian U19 Championship]]\n** '''2006''' [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2006 Asian Junior Men's Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian U21 Championship]]\n** '''2007''' [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2007 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]]\n** '''2008''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2008 Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|AVC Asian Cup]]\n** '''2009''' [[File:Silver medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2009 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian Championship]]\n** '''2010''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2010 Asian Men's Volleyball Cup|AVC Asian Cup]]\n** '''2010''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2010 Asian Games \u2013 Men|Asian Games]]\n** '''2011''' [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2011 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2013 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian Championship]]\n** '''2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|Asian Games]]\n** '''2017''' [[File:Simple bronze cup.svg|16px]] [[2017 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Grand Champions Cup|FIVB World Grand Champions Cup]]\n** '''2018''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2018 Asian Games \u2013 Men's tournament|Asian Games]]\n** '''2019''' [[File:Gold medal asia.svg|16px]] [[2019 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|AVC Asian Championship]]\n\n===Individually===\n*'''Best Spiker:''' [[2005 FIVB Volleyball Boys' U19 World Championship|2005 U19 World Championship]]\n*'''Best Blocker:''' [[2006 Asian Junior Men's Volleyball Championship|2006 Asian U21 Championship]]\n*'''Best Blocker:''' [[2007 Asian Men\u2019s Club Volleyball Championship|2007 Asian Club Championship]]\n*'''Best Blocker:''' [[Volleyball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's qualification#3rd tournament|2008 3rd World Olympic Qualification Tournament]]\n*'''Best Blocker:''' [[2009 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2009 Asian Championship]]\n*'''Best Blocker:''' [[2010 FIVB Men's Club World Championship|2010 Club World Championship]]\n*'''Best Blocker:''' [[2013 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|2013 Asian Club Championship]]\n*'''Best Blocker:''' [[2013 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2013 Asian Championship]]\n*'''Best Middle Blocker:''' [[2014 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|2014 Asian Club Championship]]\n*'''Best Middle Blocker:''' [[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2015 World Cup]]\n*'''Best Middle Blocker:''' [[Volleyball at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's qualification#1st tournament|2016 1st World Olympic Qualification Tournament]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Canada claim final Olympic ticket in Tokyo men\u2019s qualifier|url=http://worldoqt.japan.2016.men.fivb.com/en/news/canada-claim-final-olympic-ticket-in-tokyo?id=61749|publisher=[[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Volleyball]]|accessdate=5 June 2016}}</ref>\n*'''Best Middle Blocker:''' [[2016 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|2016 Asian Club Championship]]\n*'''Best Middle Blocker:''' [[2017 Asian Men's Club Volleyball Championship|2017 Asian Club Championship]]\n*'''Best Middle Blocker:''' [[2019 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship|2019 Asian Championship]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.fivb.org/en/volleyball/Competitions/WorldClubChampionships/2009/Players.asp?Tourn=MCLUB09&Team=PAY&No=117483 FIVB profile]\n* [http://worldoqt.japan.2016.men.fivb.com/en/teams/iri-iran/players/seyed-mohammad-mousavi-eraghi?id=50731 Player profile at World Olympic Qualification tournament]\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/2100500.html PlusLiga player profile]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{succession box\n  | before = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|USA}} [[Maxwell Holt]]<br> {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Lucas Saatkamp]] \n  | title = Best Middle Blocker of <br>[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n  | years = [[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2015]]<br /> <small>ex aequo {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sebasti\u00e1n Sole]]</small>\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title       = Iran squads\n|bg          = Green\n|fg          = White\n|bordercolor = #Red\n|list1       =\n{{Iran squad 2009 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2009 FIVB Men's World Grand Champions Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2010 FIVB Men's World Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2010 Asian Games Volleyball}}\n{{Iran squad 2011 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2011 FIVB Men's World Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2013 Asian Men's Volleyball Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2013 FIVB Men's World Grand Champions Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2014 FIVB Volleyball World League}}\n{{Iran squad 2014 FIVB Men's World Championship}}\n{{Iran squad 2014 Asian Games Volleyball}}\n{{Iran squad 2015 FIVB Men's World Cup}}\n{{Iran squad 2016 Summer Olympics Men's Volleyball}}\n{{Iran squad 